This memorandum, issued by President Donald J. Trump, extends the use of the National Guard to respond to the COVID-19 pandemic and facilitate economic recovery. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of cooperation between the federal government and the states in combating the spread of the virus. It acknowledges the critical support provided by the National Guard to governors in addressing the needs of vulnerable populations and fighting COVID-19 hotspots. The memorandum directs the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to fund an additional 25% of emergency assistance activities in Connecticut, in addition to the 75% federal cost share already established. This increased federal cost share will be available for orders authorizing duty through September 30, 2020. The memorandum includes general provisions and clarifies that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States. The Secretary of Defense is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.